Algorithm
Put all sticks in a min heap.
While heap size > 1:
Pop the two smallest sticks.
Add their sum to the answer.
Push the sum back into the heap.
Return the accumulated cost.

Example

Sticks = [2,4,3]

Using a min heap:

Take 2 and 3 → cost = 5
Heap becomes [4,5]
Take 4 and 5 → cost = 9
Heap becomes [9]

Total = 5 + 9 = 14

CODE-->
class Solution {
public:
    int connectSticks(vector<int>& sticks) {

        priority_queue<int, vector<int>, greater<int>> pq(sticks.begin(), sticks.end());

   int cost =0;

while(pq.size()>1){
int a = pq.top();
pq.pop();

int b = pq.top();
pq.pop();

int sum = a+b;
cost+=sum;

pq.push(sum);
}
return cost;
}
};

